20several%20years%20because%20I%20felt%20recognized%20as%20a%20whole%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThree%20weeks%20into%20working%20at%20a%20school%20in%20Colorado%2C%20I%20got%20a%20panicked%20call%20from%20my%20husband.%20My%20child%20had%20had%20a%20seizure%2C%20and%20they%20were%20on%20their%20way%20to%20the%20emergency%20room.%20I%20told%20the%20dean%20I%20had%20to%20leave%20for%20a%20family%20emergency%2C%20and%20they%20said%2C%20of%20course%2C%20I%20had%20to%20go.%20He%20recovered%2C%20but%20it%20was%20scary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20setting%20boundaries.%20I%20would%20take%20time%20off%20for%20family%20commitments%2C%20and%20if%20there%20was%20a%20day%20care%20issue%2C%20I%20would%20bring%20my%20son%20to%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20team%20was%20very%20accommodating.%20But%2C%20ultimately%2C%20I%20left%20for%20a%20higher-paying%20position.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ab2d81e4-3f17-45f3-9cc2-2e3388fcd114%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI've%20changed%20my%20approach%20to%20job%20interviews%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20realized%20that%20if%20you%20set%20boundaries%2C%20there%20are%20workplaces%20that%20respect%20that.%20Figuring%20out%20the%20work%20culture%20became%20a%20key%20part%20of%20my%20job%20applications.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20interviews%2C%20I%20bring%20up%20my%20family%20right%20away%20and%20talk%20about%20the%20family%20activities%20that%20are%20important%20to%20me.%20I%20ask%20if%20the%20schedule%20is%20flexible.%20I'm%20clear%20with%20my%20employer%20about%20what%20they%20are%20getting%20from%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20ask%20a%20lot%20about%20a%20job%20and%20what%20it%20means%20to%20be%20successful%20in%20that%20position.%20If%20somewhere%20has%20a%20%26quot%3Bwork%20hard%2C%20play%20hard%26quot%3B%20motto%2C%20I%20know%20it's%20not%20for%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223caf80cc-ede3-497a-9d1a-fd5307964e91%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20have%20to%20take%20responsibility%20for%20setting%20boundaries%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20have%20to%20have%20the%20confidence%20to%20set%20boundaries.%20A%20couple%20of%20years%20ago%2C%20I%20had%20to%20get%20a%20flight%20to%20a%20work%20meeting.%20I%20realized%20the%20timing%20meant%20I'd%20miss%20my%20son's%20basketball%20game.%20I%20changed%20my%20flight%20to%20watch%20his%20game%20and%20flew%20overnight%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20takes%20bravery%20to%20say%20to%20your%20workplace%3A%20%26quot%3BI'm%20adjusting%20my%20flight%2C%20and%20here's%20why.%20And%20this%20is%20non-negotiable%20for%20me.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20I%20work%20for%20a%20school%20with%20job%20flexibility%3A%20three%20days%20on%20campus%20and%20two%20days%20from%20home.%20I%20take%20off%20days%2C%20like%20my%20son's%20first%20day%20of%20school.%20I%20learned%20it's%20OK%20to%20prioritize%20these%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20manage%20a%20team%20of%20eight%2C%20and%20setting%20a%20good%20example%20for%20them%20is%20important.%20You%20don't%20have%20to%20choose%20between%20growing%20your%20career%20and%20having%20a%20personal%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20used%20to%20fear%20setting%20a%20boundary%20or%20saying%20no%20to%20an%20unreasonable%20work%20request%20would%20mean%20I%20wasn't%20a%20team%20player%20and%20didn't%20care%20about%20my%20job.%20That's%20simply%20not%20true.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20love%20my%20work%20and%20work%20hard%2C%20but%20it's%20just%20a%20part%20of%20who%20I%20am%20%E2%80%94%20not%20my%20entire%20identity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEditor's%20note%3A%20Business%20Insider%20reached%20out%20to%20the%20university%20where%20Shafenberg%20was%20discouraged%20from%20taking%20time%20off%20and%20asked%20to%20return%20from%20maternity%20leave%20early%20for%20comment.%20The%20university%20has%20since%20merged%20with%20another%20institution%2C%20the%20current%20press%20team%20said%20they%20cannot%20comment%20on%20the%20university's%20practices%20before%20the%20merger.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%26quot%3BThe%20sentiments%20expressed%20by%20your%20interviewe