boasted%20about%20their%20plans%20for%20a%20sexy%2C%20innovative%20app%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsports-gambling-sportsbook-wall-street-betting-hedging-2024-5%3Famp%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eonline%20sports%20betters%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20a%20UX%20designer%2C%20my%20job%20would%20be%20to%20transition%20their%20brick-and-mortar%20business%20into%20the%20digital%20landscape.%20I%20was%20a%20bright-eyed%20young%20designer%20and%20the%20only%20one%20with%20casino%20design%20experience%2C%20so%20I%20felt%20confident%20in%20my%20ability%20to%20bring%20the%20product%20to%20new%20heights.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b4e67317-8793-4b27-ac0e-d74b404511f7%5C%22%3EThe%20company%20didn't%20value%20my%20expertise%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20brought%20my%20team%20some%20initial%20design%20ideas%20alongside%20an%20expected%20timeline%2C%20to%20which%20I%20was%20met%20with%20high%20praise%20among%20my%20design%20colleagues.%20But%20as%20my%20ideas%20made%20it%20through%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbayer-bill-anderson-ceo-corporate-hierarchy-get-rid-of-bosses-2024-4%3Famp%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elayers%20of%20bureaucracy%20%3C%2Fa%3Eand%20further%20away%20from%20folks%20with%20design%20experience%2C%20I%20faced%20pushback.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20old-school%20exec%20team%2C%20made%20up%20mostly%20of%20older%20men%2C%20didn't%20seem%20to%20have%20a%20fundamental%20understanding%20of%20what%20it%20took%20to%20build%20an%20app%20and%20therefore%20hadn't%20put%20aside%20the%20time%20or%20money%20to%20make%20it%20a%20reality.%20We%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foverworked-underpaid-never-getting-taken-advantage-of-again-2023-7%3Famp%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunderstaffed%20and%20underresourced%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20they%20were%20unwilling%20to%20amend%20that%20if%20it%20meant%20diverging%20from%20their%20rigid%2C%20profit-driven%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20began%20feeling%20pigeonholed%20into%20creating%20a%20dated%2C%20basic%20platform%20that%20was%20a%20far%20cry%20from%20the%20innovation%20they'd%20promised.%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20fighting%20to%20have%20my%20opinion%20heard.%20I%20was%20the%20youngest%20person%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleading-women-in-tech-discuss-how-women-are-transforming-the-industry-2023-3%3Famp%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eonly%20woman%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20most%20conversations%2C%20which%20made%20it%20even%20more%20difficult%20to%20find%20my%20footing%20in%20the%20company.%20No%20one%20with%20any%20pull%20seemed%20willing%20to%20advocate%20for%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20months%20of%20biting%20my%20tongue%2C%20a%20male%20coworker%20and%20I%20decided%20to%20voice%20our%20concerns%20to%20managers%20that%20the%20app%20wouldn't%20land%20well%20with%20users%20in%20its%20current%20state%20%E2%80%94%20and%20we%20were%20met%20with%20an%20angry%20warning%20not%20to%20jeopardize%20the%20launch%20of%20the%20product.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20UX%20designer%2C%20it's%20my%20job%20to%20be%20the%20voice%20of%20the%20user%2C%20so%20it%20felt%20like%20they%20were%20questioning%20my%20competence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20week%2C%20the%20coworker%20who%20I'd%20confronted%20my%20bosses%20with%20told%20me%20he%20received%20an%20apology%20and%20that%20I%20should%20expect%20one%20soon.%20I%20never%20heard%20a%20word.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2225c9a27f-d7ed-493a-b7b7-427ccce0d619%5C%22%3EI%20still%20question%20if%20my%20age%20and%20gender%20played%20a%20role%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wouldn't%20say%20I%20faced%20any%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdiscrimination-at-work-women-all-ages-jobs-hiring-employer-bosses-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eblatant%20ageism%20%3C%2Fa%3Eor%20sexism%20at%20the%20company%2C%20but%20the%20constant%20disregard%20for%20my%20opinion%20and%20absence%20of%20an%20apology%20felt%20targeted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20flooded%20with%20internal%20turmoil%20as%20I%20flipped%20through%20contrasting%20narratives%20in%20my%20head.%20%3Cem%3EMaybe%20they%20are%20listening%20and%20I%20just%20don't%20make%20sense%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20or%20%3Cem%3Emaybe%20I'm%20just%20jaded%20and%20they're%20right.%3C%2Fem%3E%20I%20couldn't%20seem%20to%20get%20a%20grip%20on%20reality.%20All%20I%20knew%20was%20I%20was%20feeling%20pure%20feminine%20rage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20stayed%20with%20the%20company%20to%20pay%20my%20bills%20and%20fund%20my%20graduate%20degree%2C%20but%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquiet-quit-plan-months-burnout-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ementally%2C%20I%20withdrew%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20got%20my%20work%20done%20quietly%20and%20stopped%20inserting%20my%20opinion%20when%20it%20wasn't%20asked%20for.%20I%20started%20receiving%20negative%20feedback%20in%20November%20about%20my%20lack%20of%20commitment%20to%20the%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20month%2C%20I%20was%20awaiting%20my%20annual%2010%25%20salary%20increase%20when%20I%20was%20informed%20that%20I%20wouldn't%20be%20receiving%20it.%20They%20told%20me%20that%20my%20performance%20was%20declining%2C%20but%20when%20I%20asked%20for%20specific%20markers%20of%20underperformance%2C%20they%20came%20back%20empty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20realized%20there%20was%20no%20way%20to%20win.%20I'd%20be%20punished%20for%20speaking%20my%20opinion%20and%20punished%20for%20staying%20quiet.%20I%20put%20my%20two%20weeks%20in%20that%20week%20and%20decided%20I%20was%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fe397932-69fc-4df2-a907-b504eb7a5a24%5C%22%3EIt%20wasn't%20easy%20to%20leave%20the%20comfort%20of%20corporate%20life%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20realized%20that%20climbing%20the%20corporate%20ladder%20wasn't%20possible%20unless%20I%20sacrificed%20my%20identity%20and%20better%20judgment%20to%20join%20a%20company's%20mission%20for%20profit.%20I%20knew%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%2