Journal%3C%2Fem%3E%20reporter%20Evan%20Gershkovich%20and%20former%20US%20marine%20Paul%20Whelan%2C%20along%20with%2014%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20press%20statement%2C%20US%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Antony%20Blinken%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BUnder%20President%20Biden's%20leadership%2C%20we%20have%20secured%20the%20release%20of%20dozens%20of%20Americans%20who%20were%20held%20hostage%20or%20wrongfully%20detained.%26quot%3B%20This%20set%20the%20tone%20for%20a%20political%20show%20of%20strength%20by%20the%20Democrats%20in%20the%20upcoming%20days%20as%20the%20party%20prepares%20for%20its%20big%20event%20in%20Chicago%2C%20the%20Democratic%20National%20Convention%20on%20August%2019%2C%20where%20President%20Biden%20will%20be%20making%20his%20baton-handing%20speech.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Win%20To%20Show%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20prisoner%20swap%20provides%20him%20with%20the%20perfect%20opportunity%20to%20show%20that%20his%20administration%20got%20work%20done%20while%20the%20Republican%20nominee%20Donald%20Trump%20made%20false%20claims.%20What%20gives%20Biden%20a%20shot%20in%20the%20arm%20is%20that%20Trump%20had%20claimed%20that%20Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20would%20release%20Evan%20Gershkovich%20for%20him%20but%20not%20for%20anyone%20else%20(by%20which%20he%20meant%20President%20Biden%2C%20who%20was%20still%20running%20for%20a%20second%20term%20in%20May%20when%20Trump%20made%20this%20claim).%20He%20has%20been%20proven%20wrong%20in%20less%20than%20three%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESocial%20media%20was%20abuzz%20with%20celebratory%20notes%20around%20the%20release%20of%20Gershkovich%2C%20and%20it%20was%20Eric%20Columbus%2C%20litigator%20for%20Speaker%20Nancy%20Pelosi%2C%20whose%20X%20post%20drew%20attention%20to%20the%20comparison%20between%20Biden%20and%20Trump%20when%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BTrump%20loses%20his%20hostage%20as%20Evan%20Gershkovich%20is%20released.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETrump's%20Response%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Trump%20remained%20at%20his%20combative%20best%2C%20asking%20why%20details%20of%20the%20prisoner%20swap%20were%20not%20shared%20yet.%20He%20wrote%20on%20Truth%20Social%20-%20%26quot%3BHow%20many%20people%20do%20we%20get%20versus%20them%3F%20Are%20we%20also%20paying%20them%20cash%3F%20Are%20they%20giving%20us%20cash%20(Please%20withdraw%20that%20question%2C%20because%20I'm%20sure%20the%20answer%20is%20NO)%3F%20Are%20we%20releasing%20murderers%2C%20killers%2C%20or%20thugs%3F%20Just%20curious%20because%20we%20never%20make%20good%20deals%2C%20at%20anything%2C%20but%20especially%20hostage%20swaps.%20%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20also%20claimed%20that%20he%20got%20back%20many%20hostages%20and%20gave%20the%20other%20country%20%26quot%3BNOTHING%20-%20and%20never%20any%20cash%26quot%3B.%20He%20also%20played%20on%20the%20point%20that%20releasing%2C%20what%20may%20be%20called%20prisoners%20convicted%20of%20serious%20crimes%2C%20would%20set%20a%20%26quot%3Bbad%20precedent%20for%20the%20future%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20those%20released%20as%20part%20of%20the%20deal%20by%20the%20Western%20governments%20-%20US%2C%20Germany%2C%20Poland%2C%20Norway%2C%20and%20Slovenia%20-%20is%20convicted%20murderer%20Vadim%20Krasikov%20from%20a%20German%20prison.%20Krasikov%20was%20convicted%20for%20killing%20a%20Georgian%20asylum%20seeker%20who%20fought%20in%20Chechnya%20against%20the%20Russians.%20He%20was%20killed%20just%20meters%20away%20from%20the%20office%20of%20the%20then-German%20Chancellor%2C%20Angela%20Merkel%2C%20in%20Berlin%20in%202019.%20Germany%20has%20called%20the%20announcement%20to%20allow%20the%20swap%20for%20Krasikov%20%26quot%3Bnot%20an%20easy%20decision%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBiden's%20'Man%20Of%20Action'%20Moment%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20US%20media%20quoted%20senior%20administration%20officials%20to%20say%20that%20German%20Chancellor%20Olaf%20Scholtz%20had%20told%20President%20Biden%20in%20February%20in%20the%20White%20House%20that%20he%20would%20agree%20to%20the%20difficult%20swap%20only%20for%20Biden.%20In%20his%20announcement%20after%20the%20swap%20was%20publicly%20announced%2C%20Biden%20thanked%20the%20allies%20including%20Turkey%2C%20which%20played%20a%20vital%20role%20in%20facilitating%20the%20release.%20He%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThis%20would%20not%20have%20been%20possible%20without%20our%20allies...%20Today%20is%20a%20powerful%20example%20of%20why%20it's%20vital%20to%20have%20friends%20in%20this%20world.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20biggest%20prisoner%20swap%20since%20the%20Cold%20War%20with%20Russia%20would%20also%20help%20Biden%20leave%20office%20asserting%20his%20diplomatic%20prowess%2C%20that%20he%20is%20a%20man%20who%20had%20the%20skill%20to%20be%20able%20to%20bring%20together%20American%20allies%20and%20partners%20in%20tough%20times.%20The%20Democrats%20would%20hope%20that%20for%20Biden%2C%20who%20is%20under%20the%20scanner%20for%20his%20stand%20in%20the%20ongoing%20Israel-Palestine%20conflict%20and%20the%20botched-up%20Afghan%20withdrawal%2C%20the%20prisoner%20swap%20that%20is%20being%20termed%20%26quot%3Bhistoric%26quot%3B%20by%20the%20US%20media%20would%20turn%20the%20attention%20to%20the%20bigger%20American%20issue%20around%20Russia.%20And%20even%20as%20Biden%20bows%20out%20of%20the%20race%20making%20way%20for%20Harris%2C%20his%20diplomatic%20legacy%20would%20not%20end%20up%20being%20a%20baggage%20too%20heavy%20for%20Harris%20to%20carry%20into%20November.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Maha%20Siddiqui%20is%20a%20journalist%20who%20has%20extensively%20reported%20on%20public%20policy%20and%20global%20affairs.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722586800000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-08%2Fq6e1995_prisoner-swap_625x300_02_August_24.jpg%22%2C%22