3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Padmashree%20Pande.%20All%20photos%3A%20Minal%20Karanwal.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722498878000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2FBalika-panchayat-2_11zon-1722331557.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D359001%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22IAS%20Minal%20Karanwal%2C%20chief%20executive%20officer%20of%20Nanded%20Zila%20Parishad%2C%20has%20introduced%20the%20concept%20of%20%E2%80%98Balika%20Panchayat%E2%80%99%20in%20Nanded%20district%20of%20Maharashtra.%20It%20helps%20young%20girls%20become%20active%20citizens%20who%20are%20able%20to%20target%20and%20address%20local%20issues.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Shivani%20Gupta%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F359001%2Fias-officer-balika-panchayat-nanded-maharashtra-young-girls-fight-alcoholism-child-marriage%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98We%20Were%20Born%20To%20Stand%20Out%E2%80%99%3A%2032%20People%20With%20Autism%20Share%20What%20They%20Need%20the%20World%20to%20Understand%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EWhen%20Tanya%20Joseph%20(15)%2C%20who%20identifies%20as%20an%20individual%20with%20non-speaking%20autism%20was%20asked%20if%20she%20could%20change%20anything%20about%20her%20situation%2C%20she%20didn%E2%80%99t%20flinch%20a%20second%20before%20writing%20down%20her%20response%2C%20%E2%80%9CIf%20I%20were%20to%20do%20that.%20I%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20be%20Tanya%20anymore.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAutism%20is%20a%20part%20of%20me%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20continued.%20Tanya%E2%80%99s%20response%20is%20a%20window%20into%20hers%20and%20the%20worlds%20of%2031%20other%20people%20diagnosed%20with%20non-speaking%20autism%2C%20who%20have%20bared%20their%20souls%20in%20the%20book%20%E2%80%98Talking%20Fingers%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESharing%20Tanya%E2%80%99s%20view%2C%20they%20believe%20that%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F60615%2Fautism-sai-connections-empowered-mothers%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eautism%20is%20not%20something%20to%20be%20wished%20away%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20an%20integral%20piece%20of%20the%20jigsaw%20which%20is%20their%20lives.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETheir%20perspective%20amazes%20me.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20research%20leading%20up%20to%20this%20piece%20introduced%20me%20to%20the%20spectrum%20of%20non-speaking%20autism%2C%C2%A0referring%20to%20cases%20in%20which%20a%20person%20with%20autism%20has%20a%20delay%20or%20difficulty%20with%20speech.%20As%20statistics%20in%20%3Cem%3EHealthline%20%3C%2Fem%3Esuggest%2C%20around%2025%20to%2030%20percent%20of%20people%20with%20ASD%20(Autism%20Spectrum%20Disorder)%20are%20minimally%20verbal.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20I%20could%20convey%20the%20essence%20of%20non-speaking%20autism%20to%20you%20through%20research%20findings%2C%20news%20publishings%20and%20heavy%20jargon.%20But%20it%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20do%20it%20justice.%20Instead%2C%20a%20sentence%20I%20read%20in%20an%20article%20published%20by%20the%20Organisation%20for%20Autism%20Research%20does%20the%20trick%20%E2%80%94%20%3Cem%3EImagine%20you%20answer%20everyone%20who%20says%20something%20to%20you%2C%20but%20only%20you%20can%20hear%20it.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWritten%20by%20Philip%20Reyes%2C%20an%20individual%20with%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F327878%2Fsejal-shah-mariposa-foundation-shares-lessons-for-raising-a-child-with-disability%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enon-speaking%20autism%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20article%20condemns%20the%20popular%20belief%20that%20non-speaking%20equals%20non-thinking.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20it%20is%20this%20very%20point%20that%20Padma%20Jyothi%20and%20Chitra%20Paul%20%E2%80%94%20both%20mothers%20to%20children%20with%2